issue.title: BUG: musi.sh not login in with Safari 13.03 or Firefox 71.0 on Mac OS 10.14.6

labels.name: bug
labels.description: Something isn't working

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**

musi.sh/apple.com are not completing Apple ID login after entering double factor authorization code in pop-up window. 
Pop up window remains white and login to musi.sh is not completed.
BUG is present/replicated on both Safari 13.03 or Firefox 71.0 on Mac OS 10.14.6


**To Reproduce**

Steps to reproduce the behavior:

1. Go to https://musi.sh/
2. Click on Connect to Apple Music
3. Sign in with your Apple ID username and password
4. If you use double factor authentication with your Apple ID, enter the verification code (sent by Apple to one of your devices) in the pop up window.
5. Pop up window turns solid white but login does not complete. 

![enter vercode1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52454/72105200-15137c00-32fb-11ea-9112-0d99cd518a68.png)

![enter vercode2 blank popup](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52454/72105309-5572fa00-32fb-11ea-8e89-980f03f5cc3f.png)


**Expected behavior**
After completing step 4 (see above) Apple ID verification is completed and you should be sent back to https://musi.sh/ logged in and continue on to listen to Apple Music.


**Screenshots**
If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.


**Desktop 
- OS: Mac OS 10.14.6]
- Browsers: Safari 13.03 or Firefox 71.0

issue.title: BUG: PLAY_ACTIVITY error in console when skipping songs

labels.name: bug
labels.description: Something isn't working

issue.body:
When I press the button to skip songs, it consistently logs this error. It seems like it's a MusicKit issue because it seems to be plaguing all other Apple Music web players. It's not super consequential, other than it occasionally plays a half-second of the beginning of the previous song or some other short hiccup before skipping properly. I just wondered if there's any way of avoiding this error, as I'm trying to use the MusitKit functionality on my own website.

issue.title: Show album released year in album details

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

issue.body:
Hi,

What is currently missing and really disappointing in Musish is that there's no album release date in album information window.
For example: https://beta.music.apple.com/ru/album/man-on-the-run-track-by-track-commentary/947975010 has it - 2014
But https://musi.sh/album/911604957 - no.

Also it looks to me that albums are not sorted anyhow or the logic is unclear. Normally albums should be sorted by the release date which luckily beta.music.apple.com/ does.
It would be really good if you could improve this.

Thank you!

issue.title: BUG: Song repeats when playing in a queue

labels.name: bug
labels.description: Something isn't working

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When songs are shuffled, before starting the next song, the song that has just been played plays again for 1-3 seconds and then only, the next song starts.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:

1. Start playing a song
2. Click Shuffle
3. Listen when next song starts

**Expected behavior**
Next song should start as and when the previous song is over.

**Screenshots**
NA

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**

- OS: Windows
- Browser Chrome
- Version v79.0.3945.79
